==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dominie
<hw>Dom"i*nie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dominus</ets> master. See <er>Don</er>, <er>Dame</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A schoolmaster; a pedagogue.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This was Abel Sampson, commonly called, from occupation as a
pedagogue, <qex>Dominie</qex> Sampson.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A clergyman. See <er>Domine</er>, 1.</def>
<mark>[Scot. & Colloq. U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dominion</ent>⟦br⟧
